node.text:
.
I happen to drive by the dump site I use to goto 2-3 day a week, so I figure I share an insight into my past.
.
15 years ago, I bought my first company truck at the age of 24. Although I was the boss, I was also the truck driver and trash hauler. When you are a small company you have to do everything and that includes picking up construction debris, hauling, and driving to the dump. I remember how awful the trash dump smells, but it helps you appreciate the better things in life.
.
I didn’t start off working at a designer’s fancy office or showroom wearing fancy clothes and looking pretty. Just a young kid with a baseball cap chasing a big dream doing whatever I can to earn a buck. Sometimes people see the image of success but don’t realize the sweat and tears behind the scenes.
.

.
.
.

A slope in the backyard can take up a lot of space that might not be functional. You can utilize retaining walls to push back the soil and create more space to make it more useable.
.
At this property we pushed the slope back 20’ to create space for a pool, guest house and outdoor kitchen. Then we utilize the height of the retaining wall to create a tall waterfeature. Win-win for creating the retaining wall.
.

.
⚠️These are purely my opinions only. If you don’t agree we can still be friends.
.
Wood floor refinishing by @gionahardwoodfloors
.
Pros: 
1) Cost effective way to change up the color of the floor vs replacing it all 
2) Relatively simple process if you rent a floor sander
3) allows a new stain color or sealer to be reapplied to old flooring
4) satisfying to watch and do
.
Cons: 
1) depends on the thickness of the existing wood or types of wood floor you might not be able to sand and refinish 
2) might look like a daunting task for some 
.
Let me know what you think or if I missed anything. DIY or D-I-Why?
.

W A P (Wrap Around Pool)
This plot was narrow but required some some creativity to put a pool in. So the pool was wrapped around the house to make it more usable.

1 side of the pool consist of pilasters with firebowl atop. The other side was custom designed arches with the lion head and water spill through the arches.
.
Then the pool was finished with thousands of mosaic to create this beautiful and exquisite look.

N A R R O W
This backyard was a challenging yard because it was very narrow yet long. We decided to section the yard into multiple functional areas.
.
The first third we built a floating pad surrounded by water for a place to do yoga or meditate with the fountain walls.
.
The second area was a zero edge pool with a sunken fire pit next to the pool house. What is unique about this pool house is we put a spa under the roof so people can use the spa out of direct sunlight.
.
The third area we incorporated a circular rose garden with a checkered pattern pathway leading up to the iron gazebo.
.
One yard but multi functional. Which area is your favorite?
.
